public class MemorySearchable
extends BaseFeatureClass

Stores and manages Identifiable Spatial Data, such as, Features or graphic Elements in memory. You can add/delete the data using the addData and removeData methods. All data added, are stored in a spatial index that is kept in memory.

Note: Do not store too many features this way, as you will quickly run out of memory.

This class is a subclass of BaseFeatureClass, and takes advantage of its search strategy. Identifiable object's DataID must be set before it's added to MemorySearchable since the DataID will be used as a key to store/retrieve the Identifiable object

See Also:
Feature, Element
